    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - HUBS, BEARINGS, AND SEALS - HUB ASSEMBLY - REPLACE HUB
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="0">
        <title>REPLACE HUB</title>
        <para>To replace old hub with new hub, it is recommended that all new wheel studs be installed. Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s14001t_18.xml" xrefid="hl1400111">HUB WHEEL STUD, Install
                <xref refid="hl1400111"/>
            </hotlnk>
            , described in above steps. If the old bearings are in good condition and are to be re-used, refer to
            <hotlnk document="s14001t_3.xml" xrefid="hl1400102">BEARING CUP, REMOVE,
                <xref refid="hl1400102"/>
            </hotlnk>
            AND
            <hotlnk document="s14001t_4.xml" xrefid="hl1400103">BEARING CUP, INSTALL
                <xref refid="hl1400103"/>
            </hotlnk>
            .
        </para>
    </svcproc>
